<HL>
   Business Brief -- Canadian Pacific Ltd.:
   Michael DeGroote, Director,
   Sells Most of His Holdings
</HL>
<DATE>
06/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CP LDMFA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Michael DeGroote, chairman and chief executive of Laidlaw
Inc. sold all but 2,000 shares of his 1.9% stake in Canadian
Pacific Ltd.
   Canadian Pacific is a Montreal-based industrial holding
concern, which owns one of Canada's two railroads and also
has interests in the energy and telecommunications
industries. Laidlaw is a transportation and waste-management
concern based in Burlington, Ontario.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   RBC Dominion Securities Inc. and Gordon Capital Corp.
purchased a total of 6,104,467 shares from Mr. DeGroote for
distribution to buyers on the Toronto and Montreal stock
exchanges at 22 Canadian dollars (US$18.77) a share.
   In trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange, Canadian Pacific
closed at C$21.75, down 75 Canadian cents.
   Mr. DeGroote acquired a total of 12.1 million shares in
Canadian Pacific when he sold it his controlling stake in
Laidlaw.
   Neither Mr. DeGroote nor other Laidlaw officials could be
reached for comment.
</TEXT>
